  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      All neuropathic chronicle pains are difficult to treat. Currently many patients are not
      relieved by electric stimulations of central nervous system, existing. Recently cortical
      stimulation had a development important and benefit effects are proven. In this study we
      evaluate medico-economic impact of this treatment.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
